<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2254] Support more queries (other than just title) in Trec quality pkg</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2254</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Now that we can properly parse descriptions and narratives from TREC queries (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2210&quot; title=&quot;trectopicsreader doesn&amp;#39;t properly read descriptions or narratives&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2210&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), it would be nice to allow the user to easily run quality evaluations on more than just &quot;Title&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch adds an optional commandline argument to QueryDriver (the default is Title as before), where you can specify something like:&lt;br/&gt;
T: Title-only&lt;br/&gt;
D: Description-only&lt;br/&gt;
N: Narrative-only&lt;br/&gt;
TD: Title + Description,&lt;br/&gt;
TDN: Title+Description+Narrative,&lt;br/&gt;
DN: Description+Narrative&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The SimpleQQParser has an additional constructor that simply accepts a String[] of these fields, forming a booleanquery across all of them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
